description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Senior Mental Health Practitioner (RMN, OT, SW or equivalent)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Band:&lt;/strong&gt; Band 6 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours:&lt;/strong&gt; 37.5 hours per week &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department: &lt;/strong&gt;Andover Community Mental Health Team &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; 68b Junction Road, Andover &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a talented and experienced mental health nurse, occupational therapist or social worker? Do you want a chance to make a positive impact on patients, service users and their families in Andover? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If so, look no further! This is a rare opportunity for an enthusiastic, dedicated and highly motivated individual to join our busy but friendly team in Andover. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a team who really care about staff members and making sure that they are well looked after and supported by offering regular supervision, reflective practice and providing continuous training, educational, and development opportunities. The team culture has a strong focus on staff wellbeing and looking after one another. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need to have experience of working with adults with mental health needs and have a strong interest in working with service users with severe and enduring mental health issues in a community setting. We work within a recovery focused model and strive to provide evidence based interventions to support recovery. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your main responsibilities are: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coordinate care for patients with severe and enduring mental health problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participate in the teams “shared care” rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunity to run a nurse led clinic, depot clinic and or facilitate groupwork programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care coordinate personalised packages of care, which require involvement of other agencies, as well as producing Tribunal reports, completing assessments and reviews of care, supervising junior staff and mentoring nursing students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Able to use your own initiative and organise your time efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good working knowledge of CPA processes and sound knowledge of safeguarding processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to identify issues and problem solve, seeking support when necessary. .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have excellent assessment and communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Must be a team player&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sound IT skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Car driver and use of car within work hours is essential.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;For an informal visit and discussion, please contact Liz White (Team Leader) or Mandy James (Team Manager) on 01264 364180.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
